title: For Sale:  Sig Sauer p226 Special Configuration Model
postcontent:
I purchased this Sig Sauer almost 6 months ago (first owner). I fired about 50-75 rounds through it just to see how it shoots since it was my first Sig. This is a Special Configuration Model, before purchasing the firearm I called Sig Sauer customer service, gave them the serial number of the firearm and asked them what makes it a "special configuration" model. Sig customer service informed me that this pistol was specifically ordered by the military (branch of military is unknown) and Sig Sauer either made more then what was requested by the military, or the military decided they didn't need as many as originally estimated. Due to this mistake sig sauer labeled these type of firearms as Special Configuration Model's meaning their military surplus. This model is very hard to find especially in local gun shops due to the special configuration label and because it does not have a rail (keeps the classic look). To my knowledge Sig Sauer stopped producing the p226 without the rail, the only p226 that can be purchased now come standard with the rail.

As you can see in the picture this firearm is flawless, there is absolutely no scratch on this thing at all. I have kept it in great condition fired just a few rounds out of it and mostly its been sitting under my bed. It comes with two magazines (original), box, and lock. Night sights came with the firearm out of the factory. The firearm also comes with E2 grips meaning they are interchangeable if you have larger or smaller hands you can find a grip that will fit you. It is chambered in .40 S&W.

I will also be including in this price TWO custom made holsters by TTgunleather. I payed over $300 just for the holsters. ONE holster is custom made for the firearm the other is custom made for the magazine. Both holsters have been crafted from genuine Cayman Lizard and look amazing. I have included pictures of the holsters in natural day light. I received the holsters on the 8th of September so they are brand new, it took 4 months to complete. 

The reason I'm even considering selling this firearm is to upgrade to a .45. On the other hand I am in no rush to sell it, the ad will stay up until the firearm is sold or until I change my mind and decide to keep it. My price is FIRM. I'm not interested in trades, I will not sell any of the items here individually they will all be sold together in this package.

title: For Sale/Trade:  FRANCHI SPAS 12 (Semi Auto Shotgun)
postcontent:
This is a pre-ban Franchi import by FIE with the original hook stock. The SPAS-12 is a combat shotgun that was manufactured by the Italian firearms company Franchi S.p.A. from 1979 to 2000. The SPAS-12 is a dual-mode shotgun, meaning it can be calibrated to cycle either semi-automatically or through pump-action. The SPAS 12 was designed to function primarily as a semi-automatic firearm, with the pump-action mode used to reliably fire low-pressure ammunition such as tear gas rounds or less-lethal bean bags. Switching between firing modes is done by pressing a button under the foregrip, and sliding the foregrip slightly forward. This is one has a 1987 date code. These guns are pretty rare and hard to find, only 1,850 were imported. I

I have placed Talon grips on the fore grip to help when in pump mode, it can easily be removed.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Military collectors! Mannlicher M95 8mm x 56R Long Rifle
location: West STL County, St. Louis, Missouri
postcontent:
For sale I have a Straight pull Hungarian 8mm x 56R M95 Mannlicher rifle complete in well used condition. I bought this at an auction of antique firearms last year and never had the time to take it out to shoot it. Bore is good and it seems to be operable.
This rifle was made by the Budapest works in 1914. The full length rifle is somewhat scarce as most were cut down to carbine length. 
Sometime during its service use a trooper named Guillot carved his name in the stock. 
That is what stirred me to buy this, wondering about this soldier Guillot and what he and the rifle might have experience in WWI or WWII.
No sling or bayonett.
 Has one charger clip included. Clips are available through on-line sources (eBay, gunbroker, etc..) 

Sell gun for $175 OBO 
Also have 8 boxes of 8mm x 56R Privi ammo. Gun and ammo $250.

This is my dad's listing and he's been out of town and has not been able to follow up on some previous inquiries so we'll go at it again Thanks for looking.

postcontent:
Here are some of the items in my safe I may be willing to trade away for the things I'm looking for below.  I will gladly send detailed pictures to anyone interested, once they've told me what they have for trade.

1. Beretta 92FS Compact L 9mm pistol.  This is the shorter barrel, shorter-gripped, 13-rd version of the 92FS.  It'll come with two sets of grips, 4 magazines, a lightweight D hammer spring already installed, and a very low round count.  This pistol is nearly new and looks it.  Black finish.

2. Swiss K35 rifle, 7.5 x 55mm caliber.  Rifle is in great shape, and will come with some brass and maybe a few rounds of ammo (have to see what I have for it).  These have a reputation for great accuracy.  Straight-pull bolt action.

3. Beretta 86FS Cheetah, semi-auto .380 pistol with tip-up barrel.  Will come with (3) 8-rd magazines.  This is a collector's item these days.  Pistol is a shooter, and great for anyone who isn't strong enough to rack the slide on a standard semi-auto.

4. Remington 40X smallbore .22 LR rifle.  This is the early version.  "US" marked, with Redfield iron sights.  Rifle is in good shape.

5. Beretta 92G 9mm pistol.  Same as the 92FS, except that the decocker lever doesn't have a "Safe" position.  It's spring-loaded, and will spring back to "off safe" when released.  These are fairly rare and sought after for competition and defensive use.  Has a D hammer spring installed to reduce trigger weight.  Will come with (4) 15-rd magazines.

6.  Beretta 92 Practice Kit for .22 LR.  Will include (2) magazines and complete barrel/slide assembly.  Can be used on any full-size Beretta 92 series pistol.  The kit probably has had 200 rounds through it, and still looks new.

7. Double Star AR lower.  This is a stripped aluminum lower which is new in the box.

8. There are various Beretta 92 accessories which I'll give options to buy/trade for to the people who take the 92's.  These accessories include grips, multiple magazines, holsters, extended slide release, etc.

NOTE:  Yes, I may be willing to sell some of these, but I'd prefer to trade them instead.  Cash prices will be on the high side.  

NOT INTERESTED IN SHIPPING.  PLEASE DO NOT CONTACT ME ABOUT ANY OF THIS IF YOU ARE OUT OF STATE OR CAN'T MEET ME FACE-TO-FACE.   I will travel within VA to meet you, distance depends on what you have to offer.
